FBIS4-62891 "drsov097_h_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 Moldova Snegur Joins Moldovan Agrarian Democratic Party Snegur Joins Moldovan Agrarian Democratic Party AU1905065094 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 1900 GMT 18 May 94 AU1905065094 Bucharest Radio Romania Network Romanian BFN [Text] Mircea Snegur, president of the Republic of Moldova, has decided to join the Moldovan Agrarian Democratic Party [PDAM], winner of the parliamentary elections that took place two and a half months ago, our correspondent Alexandru Beleavschi reported, quoting sources in the Moldovan Presidency. Thus, President Snegur's decision makes it possible today for all Chisinau's leaders to be united under the banner of the PDAM. Prime Minister Andrei Sangheli is one of the PDAM leaders, Petru Lucinschi, president of the Moldovan Parliament, also ran on the lists of this party at the recent parliamentary elections, and Dumitru Motpan, president of the party, is the vice president of the Parliament in Chisinau.
